{"id":14881420,"mediaExerciseId":"d4c870b9-923f-4af5-afaf-77a01bd901c1","exerciseName":"21","chapterName":"13","chapterTitle":"Return, Risk, and The Security Market Line","groupId":612376,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":454,"solutions":[{"id":6005617,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine portfolio returns. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/8b407c68b31e97b01e98a379f2052511/f4d9ec05e8d2ef66de18908392872ce4/lateximg_large.png","width":798},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/8b407c68b31e97b01e98a379f2052511/f4d9ec05e8d2ef66de18908392872ce4/lateximg.png","width":398}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The **expected return** is the net income or loss that an investor predicts on investments given known interest rates.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/8b407c68b31e97b01e98a379f2052511/28ef0d1faecf89ba0a111daabf58a37b/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/8b407c68b31e97b01e98a379f2052511/28ef0d1faecf89ba0a111daabf58a37b/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's first identify the given amounts in the problem: \n\n\n| | Amount$\\hspace{5pt}$| \n|:--|--:| \n|Large-company stocks return | 12.0%|\n|Long-term government bonds return | 6.0% | \n|Small-company stocks return |16.6%|\n|Treasury bills |3.4%|\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":136,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/8b407c68b31e97b01e98a379f2052511/3a482a4b0aa209458e61ad16f2b659fd/lateximg_large.png","width":1057},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/8b407c68b31e97b01e98a379f2052511/3a482a4b0aa209458e61ad16f2b659fd/lateximg.png","width":529}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's examine at the return on a portfolio with an equal investmentÂ of large-company stocks and long-term government bonds. This is calculated by adding the totals of both security and dividing by two. This is computed as follows: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n{\\text{Expected return}}&={\\dfrac{\\text{ Large-company stocks + Long-term government bonds}}{\\text{2}}}\\\\\n&={\\dfrac{\\text{ 12.0\\% + 6.0\\%}}{\\text{2}}}\\\\\n&={\\textbf{9.0\\%}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n\n**The expected return of equal investment in large-company stocks and long-term government bonds is 9.0%.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"On the other hand, the return on portfolio that is equally invested in small-company stocks and Treasury bills is computed using the formula from step 4. This is computed as follows: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n{\\text{Expected return}}&={\\dfrac{\\text{ Small-company stocks + Treasury bills}}{\\text{2}}}\\\\\n&={\\dfrac{\\text{ 16.6\\% + 3.4\\%}}{\\text{2}}}\\\\\n&={\\textbf{10.0\\%}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n\n**The expected return of equal investment in small-company stocks and treasury bills is 10.0%.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"28228816-1281-4c4b-8f0c-a20207b1858b","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881421,"exerciseName":"22","page":454,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ff131ae3-97b0-4c7c-b369-98de9c56db68","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-questions-and-problems-22-ff131ae3-97b0-4c7c-b369-98de9c56db68"},{"id":14881422,"exerciseName":"23","page":454,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a4f498e8-7d3c-4bec-9aee-4d8aa7a2876a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-questions-and-problems-23-a4f498e8-7d3c-4bec-9aee-4d8aa7a2876a"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881419,"exerciseName":"20","page":453,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"cefc6457-4524-4007-862c-8c7bb3abb30b","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-questions-and-problems-20-cefc6457-4524-4007-862c-8c7bb3abb30b"},{"id":14881418,"exerciseName":"19","page":453,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ae7ee922-0ea4-4751-90ea-dcd87050dd82","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-questions-and-problems-19-ae7ee922-0ea4-4751-90ea-dcd87050dd82"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-questions-and-problems-21-d4c870b9-923f-4af5-afaf-77a01bd901c1"}